==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haggler
<hw>Hag"gler</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧g"gl⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who haggles or is difficult in
bargaining.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who forestalls a market; a middleman between
producer and dealer in London vegetable markets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hagiarchy</ent>⟦br⟧
